gimmick_help_str2 = '''\n\n-- If using \"Yellow Cover / Hidden\", you need to remove the slider middle and the slider end by custom skin. This function may generate negative length sliders to cover the notes. Using infinite BPM for hidden, and using the song BPM for yellow covers. You can set the slider length by filling \"Cover\", leave it blank for defaul 200, it is recommended to use a value within 500 if you are using the default slider multiplier 1.4. When the value is 500, the slider length is the entire screen range (16:9). You can use the \"Info\" function in \"Generate\" area to obtain references for numerical filling.\n
-- A spinner note is Ultra-short spinner, in scoreV2 may cause misses. Using this method will add a red line at the beginning of the map, with a default BPM of 500, This red line will affect the timing of the spinner appearance. You can use a custom BPM by filling \"Spinner\". The recommended value is between 300-800. The higher the BPM, the faster the reaction speed is required.\n
6. The custom BPM range is 0.01 ~ 1,000,000, leaving it blank uses infinity, you can also use 0 to make objects stay at the judgment point. If you use the song BPM and combine it with the \"SV green line\" function in the \"line insert\" area, you can set the object flow speed separately. For more details, please refer to the \"Lines Insert\" area guides.\n'''
lines_help_str0 = '''\nLines Insert Help\n
1. First, this area is related to the time range only, you need to fill the range before inserting.\n
2. Choose Insert / Clear / Tidy up.\n
Fill the value change, leave the volume change blank to use auto volume. Auto volume will keep the original volume of the objects, same for kiai.\n
-- SV Green Lines: You can insert a gradient SV with a range of 0.01 ~ 10. Make sure there are objects within the range before using it (yellow sliders and spins are not included).\n
-- Dense red lines: Insert red lines at a certain interval from the start time, with the interval settable. The input box is located below. The range of gradient values is also settable, with a range of 1 to 1,000,000, excluding 0. If there is an object at the exact time of inserting the line, the insertion will be shifted backward by 1ms.\n
-- Reversed line Gimmicks: This feature requires the use of the \"Gimmicks Convert\" area. Using it alone will do nothing to objects. To make objects invisible, you must first set the objects Invisible by using \"Gimmicks Convert\" area. The function is similar to Dense Red Lines, the value range is 1 ~ 1,000,000, but the insertion lines will skip within the fixed range of milliseconds of small dons and small kats. The range can be set, and the input box is located below, with a maximum of 99 and cannot be 0. It is important to note that the range is a left-closed and right-open interval. If the range is 3, the interval is [3,3), which is to prevent insertion line errors.\n
Note: In the settings, using the default values is usually sufficient. If you want to customize, please be cautious when setting the redline spacing. If you insert too many redlines, it will lead to a long insertion time. If it takes too long, the tool may become stuck, but it's not a crash; it may just be unresponsive for a while and then become responsive. It is recommended to set the range of the reversed line gimmicks to be a multiple of the redline interval.\n
-- Dense green lines: Similar to dense red lines, the value range is 0.01 ~ 10, but the lines will not be shifted backward.\n
-- SV Green Lines (BPM-Based): The value range is 0.01 ~ 10, you need to fill in the base BPM, the flow speed of the objects will be the product of the base BPM and the green line. Mainly used for live performance type maps. \n
3. \"Clear\" can clear the red/green lines within the range, and the method of clearing depends on the selected inserting mode. Choosing the first option will only clear the green lines within the range; choosing the second option will only clear the red lines within the range; choosing the third option will clear all red/green lines within the range.\n
4. \"Tidy up\" function operates on the whole map. Clicking the button to organize green lines, move the pre-placed green lines onto the objects and remove all green lines that do not cover any objects (including those used to adjust volume or kiai). Please use this function with caution.\n
5. \"Adjust SV\" is used for live performance type maps, this function operates on the whole map. All the existing green lines will be cleared, and new green lines will be inserted on each red lines (only BPM from 1 ~ 1,000,000 are included). This method ensures that the speed of all objects is consistent, according to the base BPM.\n
6. Click \"GO!\" to execute.\n'''
